Sentencas: Oxide scale formations in CH4-H2O atmospheres were compared for different alloys as interconnects in solid oxide fuel cells (Fe-Cr and Ni-Cr alloys).
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of Fe-Cr- and Ni-Cr-based alloy interconnects in CH4-H2O for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Oxidation with anode gases (CH4, H2O, CO, and CO2) caused a relatively thick oxide scale formation on the alloy surfaces even in the low oxygen partial pressures at 1073 K.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of Fe-Cr- and Ni-Cr-based alloy interconnects in CH4-H2O for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The distribution of elements in the oxide scale and the growth rates of oxide scales were precisely analyzed among the examined alloys by glow discharge optical emission spectrometry.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of Fe-Cr- and Ni-Cr-based alloy interconnects in CH4-H2O for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Mn spinels formed on the top surface of oxide scales for both Fe-Cr and Ni-Cr alloys.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of Fe-Cr- and Ni-Cr-based alloy interconnects in CH4-H2O for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Oxide scale thickness grew with annealing time by a parabolic relationship, and the growth rates were in the orders of 10(-6)-10(-5) mu m(2)
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of Fe-Cr- and Ni-Cr-based alloy interconnects in CH4-H2O for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: s(-1) at 1073 K. Ni-Cr alloy shows relatively low growth rate compared with the Fe-Cr alloy.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of Fe-Cr- and Ni-Cr-based alloy interconnects in CH4-H2O for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity after forming oxide scales was different depending on the oxide scale phases and thickness, which was on the order of 10-100 S cm(-1) at 1073 K. (c) 2005 The Electrochemical Society.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of Fe-Cr- and Ni-Cr-based alloy interconnects in CH4-H2O for solid oxide fuel cells
